# TypeScript Standards

## Module System
- Use ES2022 modules as configured in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json)
- Always use `import`/`export` syntax
- No `require()` statements

## Code Style
- Use strict TypeScript settings (as configured)
- Always define proper interfaces for API responses
- Use Zod schemas for validation and type inference
- Prefer `const` over `let` when possible
- Use descriptive variable and function names

## Error Handling
- Throw descriptive Error objects with meaningful messages
- Use try/catch for async operations that might fail
- Validate inputs using Zod schemas

## Dependencies
- Import from specific subpaths when available (e.g., `@mastra/core/agent`)
- Use the OpenAI client from `@ai-sdk/openai`
- Leverage Zod for all schema definitions

## Async/Await
- Always use async/await for Promise handling
- Avoid Promise chains in favor of async/await syntax
- Handle errors appropriately in async functions
